race.comment: BRAVE APACHE (5) has been in superb form this campaign, continuing his good run of form last start with a 0.8L defeat in a CL1 at Ascot when right in the market. He looks well placed in this event and Hearn hops back on board who guided him to victory first-up. He's clearly the one to beat. SECRET STONES (6) closed strongly from the back last start here when on the quick turnaround, finishing 1.8L off the speed. Racing well this time in work and he should be able to hold a closer position from the draw this time around. Form stacks up and he can make an impression. SANCTIONS (10) returned to Albany last start and flew home, beaten 1.7L here over the 1100m. She's since joined the Hunter yard and the inside draw today is a big tick for her chances. Back to 1000m, though her run three back rates very highly. PRINCE (3) is better than we saw last start before a break. Resumes for the new stable and can bounce back. LADY COCO (9) is some query back in trip but won well last time out.
